summary: An ordinance repealing Ordinance No. 1409 entitled: "An ordinance authorizing Jacob Furth, A. B. Stewart, J. M. Thompson, H. G. Struve, G. H. Heilbron, J. C. Haines, F. J. Grant, R. H. Denny, Bailey Gatzert, A. P. Mitten, J. P. Hoyt, and Maurice McMicken, their successors and assigns, to construct, equip, maintain and operate a system of street railways in the City of Seattle" approved June 19, 1890.
